    "question_id" : 3317381,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Collection is the main interface of Java Collections hierarchy and List(Sequence) is one of the sub interfaces that defines an ordered collection.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6111053,
      "reputation" : 1366,
      "user_id" : 4767356,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/k7xLg.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "S&#39;chn T&#39;gai Spock",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4767356/schn-tgai-spock"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 6,
    "last_activity_date" : 1476267217,
    "creation_date" : 1476267217,
    "answer_id" : 39996051,
    "question_id" : 3317381,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>List and Set are two subclasses of Collection.</p>\n\n<p>In List, data is in particular order.</p>\n\n<p>In Set, it can not contain the same data twice.</p>\n\n<p>In Collection, it just stores data with no particular order and can contain duplicate data.</p>\n"
  } ],
